Explanation:
We iterate through the string once using two nested loops. We keep a dictionary to count the occurrences of each character. If the sum of character counts is less than or equal to 2, we update the maximum length. Since the string length n is constant, the time complexity is O(n). The space complexity is O(1) as we only use a constant amount of space for the dictionary.

